# Linux System Monitoring

## Commands

- uptime
- free
- top
- ps
- df
- du

## Purpose

System monitoring helps administrators identify performance bottlenecks before users are affected.

## Common Workflow

1. Check uptime.
2. Review memory.
3. Review CPU.
4. Identify heavy processes.
5. Check disk usage.
6. Investigate before restarting services.

## Best Practice

Always collect evidence before making configuration changes.
